homeownership%20rate%20plunge%20from%2039.4%25%20to%2015.5%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPotential%20homeowners%20in%20California%20are%20increasingly%20falling%20behind%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20nation%20because%20of%20just%20how%20unaffordable%20housing%20has%20become.%20That's%20a%20trend%20that's%20been%20worsening%20over%20the%20last%20few%20decades%20and%20has%20become%20particularly%20stark%20over%20the%20last%2040%20or%20so%20years.%20About%20half%20of%20the%20state's%20declining%20homeownership%20rate%20could%20have%20been%20prevented%20if%20housing%20prices%20in%20California%20had%20stayed%20in%20line%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country%20from%202000%20to%202021%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornians%20of%20every%20age%20lag%20behind%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20being%20able%20to%20afford%20a%20house%20or%20own%20one%20outright%20without%20a%20mortgage.%20About%2046%25%20of%20people%20ages%2035%20to%2045%20in%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country%20are%20financially%20able%20to%20own%20a%20home%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study's%20analysis%20of%20the%202021%20Survey%20of%20Income%20and%20Program%20Participation.%20In%20California%2C%20just%20about%2038%25%20of%20people%20ages%2035%20to%2045%20can%20say%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20even%20as%20Californians%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FMEHOINUSCAA646N%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Egrow%20richer%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fust%2Feo%2Fbapcpa%2F20220515%2Fbci_data%2Fmedian_income_table.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eearn%20more%20than%20workers%20in%20many%20states%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fsl6yv%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title