20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20told%20me.%20While%20each%20of%20the%20men%20had%20the%20plausible%20deniability%20of%20a%20connection%20or%20two%20in%20common%20with%20her%2C%20she%20said%20it%20was%20immediately%20clear%20that%20their%20motives%20were%20not%20strictly%20professional%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20them%20worked%20in%20the%20oil%20industry%2C%20a%20field%20far%20removed%20from%20anything%20she'd%20ever%20done%20for%20a%20living.%20Someone%20else%20might%20have%20scoffed%20at%20their%20advances%2C%20but%20John%20was%20newly%20single%20at%20the%20time%2C%20and%20she%20was%20intrigued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20always%20looking%20for%20someone%20who%20has%20a%20stable%20career%2C%20who%20is%20preferably%20well%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bnot%20to%20say%20that%20I'm%20looking%20for%20sugar%20daddies%20but%20someone%20who%20can%20take%20care%20of%20themselves.%26quot%3B%20On%20LinkedIn%2C%20she%20figured%2C%20she%20could%20fairly%20assess%20whether%20a%20romantic%20prospect's%20employment%20history%2C%20education%2C%20and%20career%20aspirations%20lined%20up%20with%20the%20kind%20of%20partner%20she%20envisioned%20for%20herself.%20At%20the%20very%20least%2C%20she%20would%20know%20whether%20the%20man%20had%20a%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20other%20two%20failed%20to%20catch%20her%20interest%2C%20John%20sensed%20chemistry%20with%20the%20oil-industry%20man%20and%20decided%20to%20see%20where%20things%20would%20go.%20One%20conversation%20led%20to%20another%20until%20the%20two%20had%20spent%201%20%C2%BD%20months%20flirting%20over%20phone%20calls%20and%20text%20messages.%20It%20was%20during%20that%20phase%20of%20the%20relationship%20that%20John%20posed%20a%20question%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40sheissamme%2Fvideo%2F7199823801151130926%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eon%20TikTok%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%26quot%3BWhy%20is%20LinkedIn%20low-key%20a%20good%20dating%20app%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20estimate%20how%20many%20of%20LinkedIn's%201%20billion%20reported%20members%20are%20using%20the%20site%20to%20find%20love.%20The%20company%20doesn't%20collect%20or%20release%20data%20on%20the%20matter%2C%20and%20its%20community-policies%20page%20prohibits%20using%20the%20platform%20for%20romantic%20advances%2C%20emphasizing%3A%20%26quot%3BLinkedIn%20is%20a%20professional%20networking%20platform%2C%20not%20a%20dating%20site.%26quot%3B%20But%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2Fdating%2Fcomments%2F1dn7uj%2Flinkedin_dating_the_unofficial_rules_or_what_they%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eplenty%20of%20posts%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.socialmediatoday.com%2Fnews%2F10-linkedin-hacks-or-things-you-didnt-know%2F523726%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Earticles%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40constancejonestv%2Fvideo%2F7013778664638729477%3Fq%3Dlinkedin%2520dating%26t%3D1700595956354%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esuggest%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsocial-media-tinder-for-work-linkedin-for-love-blurry-internet-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ELinkedIn%20users%20have%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20long%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-users-sliding-others-dms-tiktoker-dating-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eused%20the%20site%20for%20romance%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-linkedin-got-weird-work-life-blurred-lines-of-oversharing-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ELinkedIn%20use%20has%20soared%20in%20the%20age%20of%20remote%20work%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20using%20the%20platform%20to%20find%20a%20date%20has%20gotten%20more%20popular.%20But%20that%20leaves%20the%20question%3A%20Is%20it%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20mix%20work%20and%20love%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELooking%20for%20love%20on%20LinkedIn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDustin%20Kidd%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20sociology%20at%20Temple%20University%20who%20researches%20social%20media%20and%20pop%20culture%2C%20said%20that%20dating%20via%20LinkedIn%20belonged%20to%20a%20long%20tradition%20of%20%26quot%3Bdating%20hacks%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20using%20online%20tools%20designed%20for%20other%20purposes%20to%20snag%20a%20date.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20aughts%2C%20this%20happened%20with%20Friendster%20and%20then%20Myspace%2C%26quot%3B%20Kidd%20said%2C%20but%20has%20since%20spread%20to%20myriad%20platforms%20that%20are%20ostensibly%20romance-free.%20Even%20fitness-tracking%20sites%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstrava-running-dating-app-married-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EStrava%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20fair%20game.%20The%20common%20thread%20for%20love-hijacked%20social-media%20sites%20is%20a%20single%20feature%2C%20Kidd%20said%3A%20DMs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20design%20of%20LinkedIn%20helps%20to%20maintain%20its%20focus%20on%20the%20professional%2C%20but%20any%20platform%20with%20a%20direct-messaging%20option%20is%20likely%20to%20also%20be%20used%20to%20pursue%20sex%20and%20dating%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ease%20and%20relative%20privacy%20of%20direct%20messaging%20help%20explain%20%3Cem%3Ehow%3C%2Fem%3E%20some%20people%20are%20using%20LinkedIn%20for%20romance%2C%20but%20it%20doesn't%20explain%20%3Cem%3Ewhy%3C%2Fem%3E.%20In%20an%20age%20with%20so%20many%20dedicated%20dating%20platforms%20%E2%80%94%20from%20giants%20such%20as%20Tinder%2C%20Bumble%2C%20and%20Hinge%20to%20niche%20apps%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Ffeeld-app-to-find-ethically-nonmonogamous-people-to-date-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EFeeld%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(for%20the%20unconventional)%2C%20Pure%20(for%20the%20noncommittal)%2C%20and%20NUiT%20(for%20the%20astrologically%20inclined)%20%E2%80%94%20why%20mix%20Cupid's%20arrow%20with%20corporate%20updates%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20answer%20may%20be%20the%20growing%20number%20of%20Americans%20who%20have%20gotten%20tired%20of%20the%20roulettelike%20experience%20that%20comes%20with%20modern%20dating%20apps.%20In%20a%202023%20Pew%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F02%2F02%2Fkey-findings-about-online-dating-in-the-u-s%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esurvey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20US%20adults%2C%20nearly%20one-third%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20had%20used%20an%20online%20dating%20site%20or%20app%20at%20least%20once.%20More%20than%20half%20of%20women%20who%20had%20used%20the%20apps%20reported%20feeling%20overwhelmed%20by%20the%20number%20of%20messages%20they%20had%20received%20in%20the%20past%20year%2C%20while%2064%25%20of%20men%20said%20they%20felt%20insecure%20from%20the%20%3Cem%3Elack%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20messages%20they%20had%20gotten.%20Though%20an%20overwhelming%20majority%20of%20men%20and%20women%20said%20they'd%20felt%20excited%20about%20people%20they%20connected%20with%2C%20an%20even-larger%20proportion%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20were%20sometimes%20or%20often%20disappointed%20by%20their%20matches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnline%2C%20it%20isn't%20always%20easy%20to%20know%20whether%20the%20human%20behind%20an%20alluring%20profile%20is%20who%20and%20what%20they%20say%20they%20are.%20Even%20relatively%20innocuous%20virtual%20deceptions%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20outdated%20or%20ultraflattering%20photos%20of%20themselves%20that%20misrepresent%20how%20they%20look%20in%20person%20or%20fudged%20facts%20about%20their%20interests%20and%20accomplishments%20%E2%80%94%20can%20be%20disheartening.%20Then%20there%20are%20the%20people%20who%20fabricate%20or%20steal%20their%20entire%20profile%2C%20a%20practice%20known%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsigns-being-catfished-2018-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecatfishing%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20leaving%20anyone%20getting%20hit%20up%20by%20a%20stranger%20online%20justifiably%20skeptical.%20All%20these%20deceptions%20have%20left%20many%20people%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-dating-trend-online-apps-friends-romantic-partners-relationships-2023-3%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520interviews%2520conducted%2520for%2520our%2Cthe%2520person%2520they%2520eventually%2520select.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edating-app%20fatigue%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20they%20search%20for%20ways%20to%20take%20back%20some%20control%20of%20their%20romantic%20fate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn's%20appeal%20as%20a%20dating%20site%2C%20according%20to%20people%20who%20use%20it%20that%20way%2C%20is%20the%20platform's%20ability%20to%20give%20back%20some%20of%20that%20control%20and%20boost%20the%20caliber%20of%20their%20prospects.%20Because%20the%20professional-networking%20site%20asks%20users%20to%20link%20to%20their%20current%20and%20former%20employers'%20profile%20pages%2C%20it%20offers%20an%20additional%20layer%20of%20credibility%20that%20other%20social-media%20platforms%20lack.%20Many%20profiles%20also%20include%20first-person%20references%20from%20former%20colleagues%20and%20managers%20%E2%80%94%20real%20people%20with%20real%20profile%20pages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20users%20have%20taken%20this%20idea%20to%20the%20extreme.%20Last%20summer%2C%20a%20British%20expat%20in%20Singapore%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwoman-uses-linkedin-as-dating-app-roasted-unprofessional-disrespectful-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECandice%20Gallagher%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20made%20waves%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40candi.licious%2Fvideo%2F7260385706999074066%3Fq%3Da%2520grade%2520man%2520linkedin%26t%3D1702267867731%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eposting%20a%20TikTok%20video%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20which%20she%20said%20LinkedIn%20had%20%26quot%3BA-grade%20filters%26quot%3B%20for%20finding%20%26quot%3BA-grade%20men%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20namely%2C%20doctors%2C%20lawyers%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bfinance%20bros.%26quot%3B%20In%20the%20post%2C%20she%20touted%20the%20various%20filters%20you%20could%20use%20to%20track%20down%20ideal%20partners.%20More%20recently%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fjennsun%2Fstatus%2F1711809764773220547%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Escreenshot%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20tech%20entrepreneur%20George%20Hotz's%20LinkedIn%20bio%20was%20shared%20on%20X.%20In%20his%20bio%2C%20Hotz%20declared%20that%20he%20now%20used%20the%20site%20%26quot%3Bexclusively%20as%20a%20dating%20platform%26quot%3B%20and%20laid%20out%20a%20catalog%20of%20requisite%20attributes%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bintelligent%2C%20attractive%2C%20female%2C%20in%20or%20visiting%20San%20Diego%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20for%20his%20ideal%20match.%20%26quot%3BSend%20me%20a%20message%20and%20invite%20me%20out%20for%20a%20drink%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20for%20those%20who%20shy%20away%20from%20using%20LinkedIn%20to%20angle%20for%20dates%2C%20the%20site%20has%20become%20a%20go-to%20tool%20for%20vetting%20romantic%20candidates%20found%20through%20conventional%20dating%20apps%20or%20in-person%20encounters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSocial%20media%20is%20just%20one%20big%20dating%20app%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BAny%20type%20of%20social%20media%20where%20you%20can%20see%20people's%20pictures%20can%20turn%20into%20a%20dating%20app.%20And%20LinkedIn%20is%20even%20better%20because%20it's%20not%20just%20showing%20people's%20fake%20lives.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20question%20of%20consent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECharlotte%20Warren%2C%20a%2030-year-old%20content%20creator%20who%20lives%20in%20Austin%2C%20sees%20things%20differently.%20Warren%20posts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40welcometothepeasantparty%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETikTok%20videos%20about%20dating%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20has%20received%20more%20than%20her%20fair%20share%20of%20advances%20from%20unknown%20men%20on%20LinkedIn.%20Though%20she%20said%20that%20the%20men%20were%20usually%20reaching%20out%20under%20some%20flimsy%20guise%20of%20professional%20networking%20or%20%26quot%3Bmentorship%2C%26quot%3B%20many%20had%20bare-bones%20profile%20pages%20that%20suggested%20they%20weren't%20seriously%20using%20the%20platform%20for%20work.%20Several%20of%20her%20friends%20and%20colleagues%20across%20genders%20have%20received%20similar%20messages%2C%20she%20said%2C%20and%20were%20similarly%20put%20off%20by%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEveryone%20uses%20LinkedIn%20differently%2C%20but%20I%20think%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20people%20find%20it%20pretty%20invasive%20and%20inappropriate%26quot%3B%20for%20people%20to%20use%20it%20as%20a%20way%20to%20find%20romantic%20partners%2C%20Warren%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20survey%20from%20last%20year%2C%20respondents%20agreed.%20In%20May%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpassport-photo.online%2Fblog%2Fis-linkedin-the-new-tinder%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPassport%20Photo%20Online%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20asked%20more%20than%201%2C000%20female%20LinkedIn%20users%20in%20the%20US%20about%20romance%20on%20the%20platform.%20While%20the%20survey%20wasn't%20strictly%20scientific%2C%20an%20overwhelming%2091%25%20reported%20receiving%20romantic%20overtures%20or%20otherwise%20inappropriate%20messages%20on%20the%20platform.%20Three-quarters%20said%20that%20at%20one%20point%20or%20another%2C%20these%20unwanted%20advances%20drove%20them%20to%20limit%20their%20activity%20on%20the%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECaitlin%20Begg%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20organizational-communications%20consultancy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fauthsocial.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAuthentic%20Social%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20former%20LinkedIn%20employee%2C%20boiled%20the%20dilemma%20down%20to%20a%20question%20of%20consent.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20sign%20up%20for%20a%20dating%20app%2C%20I%20am%20signing%20up%20to%20get%20messages%20around%20dating.%20I'm%20open%20to%20these%20kinds%20of%20messages%2C%26quot%3B%20Begg%20said.%20On%20LinkedIn%2C%20where%20no%20such%20understanding%20is%20in%20place%2C%20those%20who%20cross%20the%20platform's%20implicit%20boundaries%20risk%20damaging%20their%20professional%20relationships%20and%20reputations.%20It's%20kind%20of%20like%20flirting%20at%20the%20office%20or%20trying%20to%20pick%20up%20dates%20at%20a%20big%20company%20off-site%20event%3A%20It%20might%20kindle%20a%20mutual%20spark%2C%20but%20it%20might%20get%20you%20fired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJan%20Yager%2C%20a%20sociology%20lecturer%20at%20John%20Jay%20College%20and%20the%20author%20of%20several%20books%20on%20friendship%20and%20dating%2C%20agreed%20that%20LinkedIn%20users%20should%20tread%20carefully%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20main%20goal%20of%20LinkedIn%20is%20professional%20relationships%20and%20career-related%20benefits.%20Anyone%20on%20LinkedIn%20has%20to%20be%20very%20careful%20not%20to%20do%20anything%20inappropriate%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20seeking%20romance%20if%20that%20is%20his%20or%20her%20goal%20%E2%80%94%20or%20it%20could%20backfire%20big%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20the%20internet%20has%20blurred%20boundaries%20between%20people's%20professional%20and%20personal%20lives%20for%20years%3A%20Warren%20met%20her%20current%20boyfriend%20on%20TikTok%2C%20and%20my%20own%20partnership%20developed%20over%20direct%20messages%20on%20Twitter%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20site%20that%20we%20both%20used%20to%20make%20professional%20connections%20and%20promote%20our%20work%20as%20journalists.%20Even%20offline%2C%20future%20couples%20can%20cross%20paths%20at%20the%20office%20or%20in%20professional%20circles.%20For%20these%20reasons%2C%20Yager%20conceded%20that%20LinkedIn%20could%20also%20fit%20the%20bill%20for%20uniting%20romance%20seekers%20in%20an%20organic%20and%20ethical%20way.%20It%20all%20comes%20down%20to%20how.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20someone%20is%20willing%20to%20take%20their%20time%20and%20let%20the%20initial%20professional%20connection%20evolve%20in%20a%20way%20that%20is%20mutually%20respectful%2C%26quot%3B%20Yager%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20if%20both%20parties%20somehow%20communicate%20their%20availability%20for%20romance%2C%20and%20they%20want%20to%20go%20the%20next%20step%20%E2%80%94%20which%20might%20mean%20a%20phone%20or%20Zoom%20call%20or%20meeting%20in%20person%20in%20a%20safe%20public%20place%20%E2%80%94%20hopefully%20it%20is%20a%20win-win.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Phone%20brain'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBegg%2C%20the%20communications%20consultant%2C%20suspects%20that%20rising%20interest%20in%20using%20LinkedIn%20for%20dating%20stems%20at%20least%20in%20part%20from%20broader%20feelings%20of%20social%20disconnection.%20For%20work%2C%20she%20researches%20how%20digital-first%20communication%20colors%20what%20people%20want%20from%20relationships.%20These%20days%2C%20she%20said%2C%20more%20and%20more%20people%20are%20craving%20slower%20and%20more%20genuine%20forms%20of%20connection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNotification%20culture%20%E2%80%94%20phone%20brain%20%E2%80%94%20has%20kind%20of%20overtaken%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Begg%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BAs%20it%20pertains%20to%20dating%20apps%2C%20I%20think%20everyone%2C%20especially%20post-COVID%2C%20has%20become%20a%20little%20bit%20jaded.%20We're%20sick%20of%20the%20same%20prompts%20from%20the%20same%20dating%20apps%20and%20the%20same%20kinds%20of%20outreach.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBegg%20has%20noticed%20more%20people%20choose%20to%20forgo%20digital%20communication%20where%20possible%20and%20seek%20out%20%26quot%3BIRL%20situations%26quot%3B%20for%20interaction%2C%20she%20said.%20Some%20of%20her%20friends%20have%20gone%20so%20far%20as%20to%20delete%20dating%20apps%20from%20their%20phones%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20meet%20people%20in%20person.%20For%20her%20part%2C%20Begg%20has%20installed%20a%20landline%20phone%20in%20her%20apartment%20to%20facilitate%20smartphone-free%20weekends%20%E2%80%94%20much%20to%20the%20delight%20of%20her%20analog-curious%2C%20film-camera-shooting%20Gen%20Z%20cousins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20LinkedIn%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20a%20digital%20platform%2C%20Begg%20believes%20that%20some%20users%20may%20be%20drawn%20to%20the%20site%20by%20their%20desire%20to%20replicate%20(or%20at%20least%20mimic)%20an%20analog%2C%20water-cooler%20experience%2C%20she%20added.%20In%20many%20real-life%20workplaces%2C%20that%20experience%20has%20been%20either%20diminished%20or%20lost%20entirely%20through%20the%20rise%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-fueling-gen-z-job-anxiety-stress-mental-health-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eremote%20and%20hybrid%20work%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20significant%20proportion%20of%20younger%20professionals%20may%20have%20missed%20out%20on%20this%20type%20of%20in-person%20workplace%20camaraderie%20altogether%2C%20which%20could%20help%20to%20explain%20LinkedIn's%20recent%20surge%20in%20popularity%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thecut.com%2Farticle%2Fwhy-teenagers-love-linkedin.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eamong%20teens%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fastcompany.com%2F90921792%2Fwhy-gen-z-is-flocking-from-twitter-to-linkedin%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E20-somethings%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20become%20so%20atomized%2C%26quot%3B%20Begg%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20what%20I%20think%20people%20are%20trying%20to%20get%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20a%20sense%20of%20collectiveness.%26quot%3B%3