520efforts%E2%80%99%2C%2520this%2520criterion%2520has%2520been%2520used%2520to%2520reward%2520states%2520with%2520higher%2520tax%2520collection%2520efficiency.%2520It%2520is%2520measured%2520as%2520the%2520ratio%2520of%2520the%2520average%2520per%2520capita%2520own%2520tax%2520revenue%2520and%2520the%2520average%2520per%2520capita%2520state%2520GDP%2520during%2520the%2520three%2520years%2520between%25202016-17%2520and%25202018-19.%5C%22%3Erecommended%3C%2Fa%3E%20forming%20a%20high-powered%20inter-governmental%20group%20to%3A%20(i)%20review%20the%20Fiscal%20Responsibility%20and%20Budget%20Management%20Act%20(FRBM)%2C%20(ii)%20recommend%20a%20new%20FRBM%20framework%20for%20centre%20as%20well%20as%20states%2C%20and%20oversee%20its%20implementation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhy-the-16th-finance-commissions-struggles-will-be-significant%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Why%20the%2016th%20Finance%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20Struggles%20Will%20Be%20Significant%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20%E2%80%98real%E2%80%99%20context%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20recommendations%20made%20by%20a%20constitutionally%20safeguarded%20Commission%20then%20there%20are%20realities%20that%20have%20a%20different%20social%2C%20political%2C%20and%20economic%20context%20layered%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20political%20economy%20of%20%3Cem%3Eactual%20%3C%2Fem%3Efiscal%20devolution%20observed%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%20has%20been%20that%20of%20extensive%20%E2%80%98politicisation%E2%80%99%20by%20the%20Modi%20Government.%20Economic%20or%20social%20criteria%20are%20hardly%20shaping%20the%20way%20the%20Union%20transfers%20funds%20to%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcentre-state-fiscal-freedom-abritrary-squeezing%5C%22%3Eargued%20recently%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20has%20been%20observed%20in%20the%20way%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcentre-state-fiscal-freedom-abritrary-squeezing%5C%22%3EModi%20government%20has%20squeezed%20some%20states%E2%80%99%20fiscal%20freedom%20to%20borrow%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%20backdrop%20of%20the%20grave%20financial%20crisis%20that%20state%20governments%20are%20facing%20currently%2C%20Kerala%20finance%20minister%20K.N.%20Balagopal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcentre-state-fiscal-freedom-abritrary-squeezing%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20his%20state%E2%80%99s%20net%20borrowing%20limits%20have%20been%20reduced%20by%20Rs%204%2C000%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20coercive%20attitude%20remains%20consistent%20in%20its%20treatment%20%E2%80%93%20and%20interpretation%20of%20clauses%20%E2%80%93%20with%20most%20non-BJP%20ruled%20states%20too.%20Recently%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcentre-state-fiscal-freedom-abritrary-squeezing%5C%22%3Ethe%20Telangana%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%20governments%20too%20made%20similar%20observations%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20need%20to%20preserve%20constitutionally%20safeguarded%20state%20autonomy%20in%20being%20able%20to%20manage%20its%20fiscal%20priorities%20(including%20for%20borrowings%20made).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20results%20in%20a%20%3Cem%3Etrust%20deficit%3C%2Fem%3E%20between%20the%20Centre%20and%20states%20and%20makes%20the%20task%20of%20any%20Finance%20Commission%20recommendations%20to%20be%20followed%20extremely%20difficult.%20Irrespective%20of%20what%20the%20FC%20says%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20can%20hardly%20be%20trusted%20at%20this%20point%20to%20see%20the%20recommendations%20being%20realised%20when%20it%20becomes%20to%20processing%20(and%20following)%20actual%20transfers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20numbers%20below%20also%20reflect%20the%20contemporary%20realities%20of%20Centre-state%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20the%20actual%20devolution%20of%20funds%20in%20Centre-state%20financial%20relations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnesinfosphere.com%2Four-work%5C%22%3Eresearch%20team%20at%20%3Cem%3EInfoSphere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(CNES)%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findia-states-welfare-spending-debt%5C%22%3Erecently%20completed%20a%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20observing%20the%20Centre-state%20fiscal%20relationship%20more%20closely.%20A%20detailed%20version%20of%20our%20findings%20was%20earlier%20discussed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findia-states-welfare-spending-debt%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Ffinminindia%2Fstatus%2F1668177996442927104%3Fs%3D51%26t%3D1vwSP919utJCl83SiqVxmg%5C%22%3Efactsheet%3C%2Fa%3E%20shared%20by%20the%20ministry%20of%20finance%20triggered%20a%20further%20investigation%20by%20our%20team%20studying%20the%20available%20data%20(from%202019%20onwards)%20on%20tax%20devolution%20%E2%80%93%20the%20share%20from%20Centre%20to%20state%20governments%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Fdrive%2Ffolders%2F1YQHxkqGrA6y8K1lXx208lIVNbA7LeSx9%3Fusp%3Dshare_link%5C%22%3Edrawn%20from%20government%20sources%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20observations%20follow%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03171140%2FTax-devolution.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22922%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03171140%2FTax-devolution.jpg%20922w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03171140%2FTax-devolution-300x174.jpg%