ho%20was%20stubborn%20and%20didn't%20think%20I%20ever%20needed%20to%20go%20to%20the%20doctor%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20even%20when%20he%20lost%20five%20pounds%20in%20a%20week%2C%20pooped%20blood%2C%20and%20shivered%20in%2090-degree%20heat%20after%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftia-clair-toomey-orr-crossfit-legend-birth-motherhood-fitness-2023-12%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECrossFit%3C%2Fa%3E%20competition%20in%20the%20August%20of%20that%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20body%20%26quot%3Bcrashed%26quot%3B%20after%20the%20competition.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20time%20I%20ate%20or%20drank%20anything%2C%20I%20would%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehave%20intense%20pain%20in%20my%20stomach%20and%20I%20would%20throw%20up.%20I%20was%20maybe%20using%20the%20bathroom%20once%20every%20couple%20days%20because%20I%20was%20barely%20having%20any%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fhow-often-should-you-poop%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebowel%20movements%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20lay%20in%20bed%20and%20look%20at%20my%20symptoms%2C%20and%20the%20bottom%20was%20always%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhat-to-know-about-colon-cancer-symptoms-diagnosis-chadwick-boseman%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecolon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20cancer.%20I%20was%20just%20like%2C%20'That%20can't%20can't%20be%20me%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthepatientstory.com%2Fpatient-stories%2Fcolorectal-cancer%2Fjj-s%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20Patient%20Story%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESingleton%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20stage%20two%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESingleton%20put%20up%20with%20these%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-red-flag-signs-symptoms-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esymptoms%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20month%20before%20his%20mom%20forced%20him%20to%20go%20to%20a%20doctor%20in%20early%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20that%20point%2C%20I%20could%20put%20my%20shirt%20up%20against%20my%20stomach%20and%20you%20could%20see%20the%20tumor%20throb%20through%20the%20skin.%20As%20soon%20as%20the%20doctor%20looked%20at%20that%2C%20he%20was%20like%2C%20'You%20got%20to%20go%20get%20a%20scan%20right%20now%2C'%26quot%3B%20Singleton%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20scan%20on%20September%204%20identified%20a%20mass%20in%20his%20colon%2C%20and%20he%20was%20sent%20for%20a%20colonoscopy%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%20After%20the%20colonoscopy%20on%20September%208%2C%20he%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20stage%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-diagnosis-young-people-gut-bacteria-microbiome-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecolon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20third%20most%20common%20cancer%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20colon%20was%2098%25%20blocked%20by%20the%20tumor%2C%20so%20he%20was%20rapidly%20sent%20for%20surgery.%20On%20September%2016%2C%20surgeons%20removed%2080%25%20of%20his%20colon%20and%2036%20inches%20of%20his%20small%20intestine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20genetic%20predisposition%20to%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20Singleton%20was%20so%20young%20and%20had%20no%20known%20family%20history%20of%20colon%20cancer%2C%20doctors%20sent%20him%20for%20genetic%20testing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20tested%20positive%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwoman-lost-25-pounds-without-diet-exercise-diagnosed-colon-cancer-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELynch%20syndrome%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20a%20genetic%20condition%20where%20a%20mutation%20in%20certain%20genes%20increases%20the%20risk%20of%20developing%20colorectal%20cancer%20by%2020%25%20to%2080%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESingleton%20shared%20his%20story%20with%20BI%20to%20raise%20awareness%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-young-people-diagnosis-causes-risk-factors-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecolon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20rates%20among%20younger%20people%20on%20the%20rise.%20Although%20Singleton's%20case%20was%20genetic%2C%20scientists%20don't%20know%20why%20the%20disease%20is%20affecting%20more%20people%20under%2050.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20joined%20a%20man's%20group%20called%20Man%20Up%20to%20Cancer%2C%20and%20they%20gave%20me%20the%20confidence%20to%20tell%20my%20story%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20important%20to%20get%20people%20educated%20about%20colon%20cancer%20even%20though%20they%20don't%20like%20talking%20about%20their%20bowel%20movements.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20sounds%20hallmark-y%20but%20advocacy%20gave%20me%20a%20purpose%20in%20life.%20It%20makes%20me%20feel%20like%20I'm%20not%20just%20wasting%20away%20as%20a%20cancer%20patient%2C%26quot%3B%20Singleton%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDespite%20chemotherapy%2C%20the%20cancer%20came%20back%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EColorectal%20cancer%20is%20usually%20treated%20with%20surgery%20to%20remove%20the%20cancerous%20tissue%2C%20and%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fbeing-organized-helped-me-through-my-cancer-diagnosis-and-treatment-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echemotherapy%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20kill%20any%20cells%20left%20if%20the%20cancer%20is%20large%20or%20has%20spread%20to%20other%20tissues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESingleton%20had%20twelve%20rounds%20of%20chemotherapy%20between%20November%202015%20and%20April%202016.%20Six%20weeks%20into%20treatment%2C%20he%20felt%20the%20throbbing%20in%20his%20abdomen%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cancer%20had%20spread%20to%20his%20abdominal%20wall%20and%20lymph%20nodes%20throughout%20his%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20next%20six%20months%2C%20I%20went%20through%20four%20different%20chemo%20cocktails%20or%20so%2C%20but%20they%20all%20failed.%20The%20cancer%20actually%20grew%20aroun