)%20an%20operational%20creditor%20(supplier%2Fcontractor%20etc.)%2C%20or%20the%20defaulting%20corporate%20itself%20may%20initiate%20CIRP%20by%20filing%20an%20application%20with%20the%20NCLT.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NCLT%20is%20an%20adjudicating%20authority%20responsible%20for%20resolving%20disputes%20related%20to%20company%20law%2C%20mergers%2C%20amalgamations%20and%20the%20winding%20up%20of%20companies%20%E2%80%95%20the%20insolvency%20resolution%20process%20of%20companies%20and%20limited%20liability%20partnerships%20under%20the%20Insolvency%20and%20Bankruptcy%20Code%2C%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResolution%20professionals%20submit%20a%20resolution%20plan%20as%20approved%20by%20the%20committee%20of%20creditors%20to%20the%20NCLT.%20The%20Committee%20of%20Creditors%20(CoC)%20may%20approve%20it%20with%20at%20least%2066%25%20voting%20for%20it.%20The%20plan%20becomes%20binding%20on%20the%20corporate%20debtor%2C%20its%20employees%2C%20members%2C%20creditors%2C%20guarantors%20and%20other%20stakeholders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20a%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fe1e33d90-9626-428a-8f15-74a031831af3%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fe1e33d90-9626-428a-8f15-74a031831af3%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1704422178567000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1BWqI_Wu0ygIBeJAncHTta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fe1e33d90-9626-428a-8f15-74a031831af3%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fe1e33d90-9626-428a-8f15-74a031831af3%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1704422178567000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1BWqI_Wu0ygIBeJAncHTta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0news%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0was%20headlined%3A%20%E2%80%98NCLT%20Mumbai%20approves%20resolution%20plan%20for%20Reliance%20Communications%20Infrastructure%20Ltd%2C%20valued%20at%20Rs%20455.9%20crore%20as%20against%20total%20admitted%20claim%20of%20Rs%2047%2C251%20crores.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnil%20Ambani%E2%80%99s%20group%20company%20had%20a%20debt%20of%20Rs%2046%2C000%20crore%2C%20with%2053%20financial%20creditors%20%E2%80%94%20including%20local%20and%20foreign%20banks%2C%20NBFCs%20and%20funds%20%E2%80%94%20laying%20claims.%20The%20NCLT%E2%80%99s%20Mumbai%20Bench%20on%20December%2019%20approved%20a%20resolution%20plan%20for%20RCIL%2C%20a%20wholly%20owned%20subsidiary%20of%20Reliance%20Communications%20Limited%20(RCOM).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETotal%20claims%20made%20by%20debtors%3A%20Rs%204%2C96%2C68%2C01%2C09%2C556%20(Rs%2049%2C668%20crore).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETotal%20claims%20admitted%20by%20NCLT%3A%20Rs%204%2C72%2C51%2C34%2C03%2C502%20(Rs%2047%2C251%20crore).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENCLT%20has%20approved%20a%20plan%20by%20which%20the%20Anil%20Ambani%20Group%20has%20to%20pay%20just%200.92%25%20of%20their%20debts%20%E2%80%95%20only%20Rs%20455.92%20crore%20of%20the%20Rs%2049%2C668%20crore%20claimed.%20The%20remaining%20Rs%2049%2C212.08%20crore%20will%C2%A0%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0be%20paid%20back%20by%20Anil%20Ambani%20%26amp%3B%20Co.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20the%20directly%20lent%20amount%20of%20Rs%20182.20%20crore%20that%20this%20group%20availed%2C%20the%20balance%20dues%20admitted%20were%20corporate%20guarantees%20and%20other%20or%20similar%20third-party%20obligations%20of%20the%20debtor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20corporate%20guarantee%20is%20an%20agreement%20in%20which%20one%20party%2C%20the%20guarantor%2C%20takes%20on%20the%20payments%20or%20responsibilities%20of%20a%20debt%20if%20the%20debtor%20defaults.%20This%20is%20often%20used%20when%20one%20of%20the%20group%E2%80%99s%20sister%20(or%20brother)%20companies%20seek%20funds%20from%20a%20financial%20institution.%20Mostly%2C%20governments%20are%20customers%20for%20infrastructure%20projects.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20performance%20or%20bank%20guarantees%2C%20there%20is%20no%20coverage%20of%20risk%20owing%20to%20non-performance%20of%20the%20developer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Filfs-downfall-banking-india-economy%5C%22%3Edemise%20of%20IL%26amp%3BFS%20four%20years%20ago%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20one%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20financial%20crises%20caused%20by%20a%20major%20conglomerate%2C%20seizing%20up%20the%20financial%20system%20and%20exhausting%20liquidity.%20The%20debt%20involved%20was%20over%20Rs%201%20lakh%20crore%2C%20of%20which%20only%20Rs%2055%2C000%20crore%20was%20addressed%2C%20leaving%2062%25%20unresolved.%20LIC%2C%20SBI%2C%20HDFC%20and%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20Orix%20Corp%20are%20some%20of%20the%20key%20stakeholders%20of%20this%20NBFC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20consider%20another%20classic%20example%20in%20which%20NCLT%20could%20not%20protect%20the%20creditors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELenders%20to%20debt-ridden%20Videocon%20Industries%20agreed%20to%20take%20a%20haircut%20of%20nearly%2096%25%2C%20the%20NCLT%20has%20observed%20while%20approving%20the%20Vedanta%20group%E2%80%99s%20Twin%20Star%20Technologies%20bid%20for%20it.%20The%20claims%20admitted%20were%20for%20Rs%2064%2C838.63%20crore%20and%20the%20resolution%20plan%20was%20approved%20for%20Rs%202%2C962.02%20crore%20%E2%80%95%20just%204.15%25%20of%20the%20claim%20amount.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20has%20happened%20in%20the%20case%20of%20bankrupt%20and%20grounded%20Jet%20Airways%2C%20where%20the%20resolution%20%E2%80%94%20in%20favour%20of%20new%20buyers%2C%20UK-headquartered%20Kalrock%20Capital%20and%20UAE-based%20Murari%20Lal%20Jalan%20%E2%80%94%20has%20taken%20over%20two%20years.%20The%20Kalrock-Jalan%20combine%20has%20agreed%20to%20pay%20financial%20creditors%20just%20Rs%201%2C183%20crore%20(7.86%25)%20over%20five%20years%2C%20against%20admitted%20claims%20of%20over%20Rs%2015%2C000%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENCLT%E2%80%99s%20performance%20can%20be%20measured%20with%20two%20different%20matrices%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERecovery%20rate%20(what%20banks%20and%20other%20financial%20institutions%20recover%20as%20a%20percentage%20of%20the%20amounts%20claimed)%20and%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAverage%20time%20taken%20by%20the%20resolution%20process.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20deeper%20look%20at%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20NCLT%20reveals%20a%20range%20of%20problems.%C2%A0Admission%20of%20cases%20often%20takes%206-12%20months%20and%20there%20are%20delays%20in%20releasing%20tribunal%20orders.%20Creditors%20file%20multiple%20applications%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20lack%20of%20consensus%20within%20the%20committee%20of%20creditors%20and%20too%20few%20NCLT%20judges%20to%20hear%20cases%2C%20which%20results%20in%20the%20pressure%20of%20multiple%20jurisdictions%2C%20and%20delay%20in%20infusion%20of%20funds%20by%20investors%20as%20envisaged%20by%20the%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20348%20cases%20resolved%20in%20NCLT%20as%20of%20March%202021%2C%20the%20average%20time%20for%20resolution%2C%20including%20litigation%20time%2C%20was%20459%20days.%20This%20is%20way%20beyond%20the%20revised%20time%20limit%20of%20330%20days%20prescribed%20by%20the%20government%20in%20July%202019.%20Prior%20to%20this%2C%20the%20expected%20timeframe%20for%20a%20resolution%20was%20270%20days.%20At%20the%20current%20pace%20of%20disposal%20of%20cases%2C%20the%20backlog%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20cleared%20in%204-5%20years.%C2%A0Why%20is%20the%20discipline%20of%20the%20law%20not%20being%20adhered%20to%20in%20full%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20on%20December%2031%2C%202022%2C%20NCLT%20had%20looked%20into%20admitted%20claims%20of%20Rs%207.91%20lakh%20crore%20lent%20by%20banks%20and%20financial%20institutions%20to%20corporates.%20Banks%20have%20written%20off%20bad%20loans%20worth%20Rs%2014.56%20lakh%20crore%20in%20the%20last%20nine%20financial%20years%2C%20from%202014-15.%20Written%20off%20loans%20to%20industries%20and%20services%20stood%20at%20Rs%207.40%20lakh%20crore.%20Only%20a%20minuscule%20amount%20from%20this%20is%20recovered%20by%20banks.%20The%20remaining%20default%20amount%20has%20to%20be%20paid%20off%20from%20the%20bank%E2%80%99s%20own%20capital%20or%20its%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20holds%20more%20than%2051%25%20of%20shares%20in%20public%20sector%20banks.%20Market%20capitalisation%20of%20the%20top%2010%20banks%20in%20India%20is%20over%20Rs%2036%20lakh%20crore.%20There%20is%20still%20enough%20left%20there%20to%20be%20looted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20too%20long%2C%20India%20has%20seen%20a%20corporate%20history%20where%20companies%20have%20failed%20but%20promoters%20have%20not.%20The%C2%A0promoters%20cannot%C2%A0and%20should%20not%20have%20a%20free%20ride%20or%20continue%20to%20master%20control%20over%20their%20company%20fraudulently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPaul%20Koshy%20is%20a%20consultant%20in%20infrastructure%20development%20and%20engineering.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%20The%20India%20Cable%20%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20updated%20and%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%20click%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftheindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704355229000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F04122517%2FUntitled-design-3.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcompanies-fail-but-promoters-dont-the-ncl