%20%E2%80%9Cunless%20there%20is%20violation%20of%20dress%20code%20of%20their%20own%20office%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20hearing%20a%20petition%20filed%20by%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20government%20against%20orders%20passed%20by%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20last%20year%20to%20summon%20two%20senior%20government%20officers.%20The%20court%20set%20aside%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20orders%2C%20including%20one%20which%20had%20directed%20the%20arrest%20of%20two%20IAS%20officers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCompelling%20the%20State%20Government%20to%20mandatorily%20notify%20the%20Rules%20by%20the%20next%20date%20of%20hearing%2C%20in%20the%20First%20Impugned%20Order%2C%20virtually%20amounted%20to%20the%20High%20Court%20issuing%20a%20writ%20of%20mandamus%20to%20notify%20the%20Rules%20proposed%20by%20the%20Chief%20Justice.%20Such%20directions%20by%20the%20High%20Court%20are%20impermissible%20and%20contrary%20to%20the%20separation%20of%20powers%20envisaged%20by%20the%20Constitution.%20The%20High%20Court%20cannot%20direct%20the%20State%20Government%20to%20enact%20rules%20on%20a%20particular%20subject%2C%20by%20a%20writ%20of%20mandamus%20or%20otherwise%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20apex%20court%20said%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EBar%20and%20Bench%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704347628000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdont-summon-govt-officials-arbitrarily-or-comment-on-their-appearance-sc-to-all-courts%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22However%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%2C%20the%20physical%20presence%20of%20government%20officials%20may%20be%20required%20in%20cases%20where%20there%20has%20been%20a%20suppression%20of%20evidence.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdont-s