1921.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fthose-involved-in-hamas-attack-signed-own-death-warrant-israel-spy-agency-mossad-chief%2Famp_articleshow%2F106531921.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22K'taka%E2%80%99s%20integral%20role%20in%20Ram%20Temple%20construction%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704341154000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106531679%2Cimgsize-69008.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fbengaluru%2Fkarnatakas-integral-role-in-ayodhya-ram-temple-construction%2Farticleshow%2F106531699.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TNN%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fbengaluru%2Fkarnatakas-integral-role-in-ayodhya-ram-temple-construction%2Farticleshow%2F106531699.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Do%20We%20Really%20Know%20About%20India's%20GDP%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F04093406%2Fmaxim-potyomkin-imviVpdI1OM-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20the%20first%20article%20in%20%E2%80%98India%20Black%20Boxed%E2%80%99.%20Read%20the%20series%20introduction%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fintroducing-india-black-boxed%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EControversy%20refuses%20to%20die%20down%20about%20the%20size%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP%20and%20its%20growth%20rate.%20It%20all%20started%20when%20the%20new%20GDP%20series%20with%20base%202011-12%20was%20released%20in%202015.%20Not%20only%20did%20analysts%20point%20to%20problems%2C%20the%20government%20itself%20was%20unhappy%20that%20it%20showed%20a%20higher%20growth%20during%20the%20UPA%E2%80%99s%20ten%20years%20compared%20to%20the%20post-2014%20NDA%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20in%202020%20severely%20dented%20the%20economy%20and%20the%20economy%20witnessed%20its%20steepest%20decline%20since%20Independence.%20The%20recovery%20from%20this%20low%20base%20was%20also%20steep.%20This%20has%20led%20to%20the%20official%20claim%20that%20India%20has%20done%20well%20in%20spite%20of%20the%20pandemic%20and%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20to%20become%20the%20fastest%20growing%20major%20economy%20in%20the%20world.%20Is%20this%20the%20correct%20picture%20of%20the%20economy%3F%20That%20depends%20on%20the%20accuracy%20of%20the%20numbers%20and%20the%20policies%20formulated%20on%20that%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPre-pandemic%20controversies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDoubts%20about%20the%20accuracy%20of%20data%20in%20the%20new%20series%20from%202011-12%20have%20risen%20on%20several%20counts.%20To%20begin%20with%2C%20when%20the%20new%20series%20was%20announced%20in%202015%2C%20there%20was%20no%20back%20series%20to%20compare%20it%20with.%20It%20was%20said%20that%20the%20new%20series%20was%20based%20on%20the%20MCA21%20data%20base%20of%20the%20industrial%20sector%2C%20which%20was%20more%20complete%20than%20what%20was%20used%20till%20then%2C%20the%20IIP%20data.%20It%20was%20stated%20that%20the%20back%20series%20could%20not%20be%20generated%20both%20because%20the%20MCA21%20data%20base%20had%20not%20stabilised%20earlier%20and%20the%20relevant%20data%20on%20employment%20became%20available%20from%202011-12.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20neither%20of%20these%20should%20have%20mattered%20since%20the%20MCA21%20data%20base%20goes%20back%20a%20long%20time%20and%20earlier%20employment%20figures%20could%20have%20been%20used%20as%20has%20been%20often%20done.%20The%20real%20reason%20appeared%20to%20be%20political.%20Namely%2C%20to%20show%20higher%20GDP%20growth%20during%20the%20NDA%20period%20compared%20to%20the%20UPA%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20controversy%20was%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20claim%20that%20the%20Indian%20economy%20grew%20at%20an%20average%20of%20about%207%25%20during%202015-2020%2C%20which%20made%20it%20the%20fastest%20growing%20large%20economy%20in%20the%20world.%20This%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hks.harvard.edu%2Fcenters%2Fcid%2Fpublications%2Ffaculty-working-papers%2Findia-gdp-overestimate%5C%22%3Eundermined%20by%20A.%20Subramanian%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2019).%20He%20showed%20that%20the%20growth%20rate%20was%20over%20estimated%20by%20up%20to%202.5%25%20after%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20blow%20came%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fnew-gdp-series-faces-fresh-questions-after-nsso-discovers-holes-1557250830351.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNEW%2520DELHI%2520%253A%2520A%2520key%2520database%2Cin%2520Asia%2527s%2520third%252Dlargest%2520economy.%5C%22%3ENSSO%20reported%20in%202019%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20out%20of%20a%20sample%20of%2035%2C456%20companies%20taken%20from%20MCA21%20data%20base%2C%2038.7%25%20were%20%E2%80%98out%20of%20survey%E2%80%99%20units.%20These%20units%20are%20either%20not%20traceable%20or%20misclassified.%20So%2C%20data%20is%20either%20missing%20or%20mis-specified.%20Thus%2C%20the%20use%20of%20MCA21%20for%20GDP%20calculation%20could%20be%20leading%20to%20errors%20in%20estimation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1571757%5C%22%3Egovernment%20argued%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20inclusion%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98out%20of%20survey%E2%80%99%20companies%20brings%20the%20output%20closer%20to%20the%20true%20production%20and%20there%20is%20no%20over-estimation%20of%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20committee%20was%20set%20up%20to%20work%20out%20the%20missing%20back%20series.%20Its%20report%20showed%20that%20the%20rate%20of%20growth%20was%20higher%20during%20the%20UPA%20period%20compared%20to%20the%20NDA%20years.%20The%20government%20rejected%20it%20and%20in%20an%20unprecedented%20move%2C%20asked%20the%20NITI%20Ayog%20to%20rework%20the%20series.%20The%20NITI%20Ayog%20obliged%20and%20presented%20a%20back%20series%20showing%20that%20the%20rate%20of%20growth%20was%20higher%20during%20the%20NDA%20period%20compared%20to%20the%20UPA%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUpward%20bias%20in%20GDP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20with%20the%20GDP%20data%20becomes%20clear%20when%20the%20official%20data%20shows%20that%20the%20highest%20rate%20of%20growth%20during%20the%20decade%20of%20the%202010-20%20was%20in%20the%20year%20of%20demonetisation%2C%202016-17.%20From%20all%20accounts%2C%20starting%20November%202016%2C%20output%20was%20severely%20impacted%20in%20that%20year.%20Even%20if%20it%20is%20assumed%20that%20the%20output%20was%20growing%20up%20to%20October%202016%2C%20and%20declined%20after%20that%2C%20the%20average%20GDP%20growth%20became%20negative.%20This%20points%20to%20the%20flawed%20methodology%20used%20to%20measure%20GDP%20which%20gave%20an%208%25%20upward%20bias%20to%20GDP%20in%202016-17.%20Even%20this%20flawed%20methodology%20showed%20the%20official%20growth%20rate%20declining%20from%208%25%20in%20Q4%20of%202017-18%20to%203.1%25%20in%20Q4%20of%202019-20.%20So%2C%20the%20real%20actual%20rate%20of%20growth%20would%20have%20become%20negative%20even%20before%20the%20pandemic%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPandemic%20and%20the%20lockdown%20severely%20impacted%20the%20economy%20in%202020%20and%20more%20particularly%20the%20unorganised%20sector.%20Subsequent%20recovery%20has%20been%20K-shaped%20%E2%80%93%20namely%2C%20some%20sectors%20growing%20while%20others%20(unorganised%20sector)%20declined.%20This%20decline%20has%20not%20been%20captured%20in%20data%20leading%20to%20over-estimation%20of%20the%20GDP.%20This%20becomes%20clear%20when%20one%20looks%20at%20the%20method%20of%20estimation%20of%20GDP%2C%20especially%20the%20quarterly%20GDP%2C%20which%20is%20what%20is%20usually%20discussed%20in%20public%20discourse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOfficial%20methodology%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fgdp-growth-the-gap-between-reality-and-rhetoric%2F%5C%22%3Ehave%20previously%20analysed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20official%20document%20which%20presents%20the%20%60Methodology%20of%20Compiling%20Quarterly%20GDP%20Estimates%E2%80%99.%20It%20mentions%20three%20factors%20that%20need%20to%20be%20noted%20regarding%20the%20calculation%20of%20GDP%20from%20the%20supposedly%20more%20accurate%20production%20side%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20production%20approach%20used%20for%20compiling%20the%20QGVA%20estimates%20is%20broadly%20based%20on%20the%20benchmark-indicator%20method.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20this%20method%2C%20for%20each%20of%20the%20industry-groups%2C%20estimates%20of%20GVA%20are%20compiled%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20general%20terms%2C%20quarterly%20estimates%20of%20Gross%20Value%20Added%20(GVA)%20are%20extrapolations%20of%20annual%20series%20of%20GVA.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20three%20points%20clarify%20that%20for%20the%20quarterly%20estimates%20of%20GDP%20based%20on%20the%20production%20approach%2C%20most%20current%20data%20are%20not%20available%20so%2C%20benchmark%20indicators%20from%20an%20earlier%20reference%20year%20have%20to%20be%20used.%20The%20last%20survey%20of%20unincorporated%20enterprises%20was%20carried%20out%20in%202015-16%20so%20that%20the%20reference%20year%20is%20now%20dated%20and%20does%20not%20capture%20the%20current%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20methodology%20states%20that%20current%20figures%20are%20obtained%20by%20extrapolations%20of%20the%20annual%20series%20of%20GVA%20of%20previous%20years.%20But%20if%20the%20previous%20year%20figures%20are%20incorrect%2C%20how%20can%20their%20extrapolation%20be%20correct%3F%20This%20has%20been%20the%20case%20post%20the%20demonetisation%2C%20introduction%20of%20the%20Goods%20and%20Services%20Tax%20and%20the%20lockdown.%20Each%20of%20these%20three%20occurrences%20administered%20a%20shock%20to%20the%20economy%20and%20caused%20disruption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20the%20procedure%20adopted%20is%20to%20make%20annual%20projections%20and%20then%20to%20divide%20them%20by%20four%20to%20give%20the%20quarterly%20figures.%20Two%20problems%20arise.%20First%2C%20there%20are%20varying%20levels%20of%20activity%20in%20the%20different%20quarters.%20For%20instance%2C%20there%20is%20heightened%20activity%20during%20the%20festive%20season%2C%20while%20it%20is%20low%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20financial%20year.%20So%2C%20division%20by%20four%20cannot%20be%20correct.%20Second%2C%20errors%20in%20the%20figures%20of%20the%20previous%20year%20get%20projected%20to%20the%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShocks%20undermine%20the%20method%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20methodology%20outlined%20above%20relies%20on%20a%20smoothly%20functioning%20economy.%20But%20it%20will%20not%20apply%20when%20there%20are%20big%20unexpected%20changes%2C%20called%20a%20shock%2C%20like%20due%20to%20demonetisation%20or%20the%20sudden%20lockdown.%20The%20shocks%20impact%20the%20basic%20parameters%20of%20the%20economy.%20Like%20the%20ratio%20of%20the%20unorganised%20to%20the%20organised%20sector%20or%20the%20real%20output%20in%20the%20agriculture%20sector.%20So%2C%20with%20a%20shock%2C%20neither%20the%20%E2%80%98benchmark-indicators%E2%80%99%20will%20be%20valid%20nor%20will%20it%20be%20correct%20to%20extrapolate%20from%20a%20normal%20year%20to%20the%20next%20one%20that%20has%20experienced%20a%20shock.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20economy%20has%20suffered%20several%20shocks%20since%202016.%20Demonetisation%20in%202016%20followed%20by%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20structurally%20faulty%20GST%20in%202017%2C%20the%20NBFC%20(non-bank%20financial%20company)%20crisis%20in%202018%20and%20finally%20the%20sudden%20lockdown%20in%202020.%20Each%20of%20them%20impacted%20the%20unorganised%20and%20the%20organised%20sectors%20differentially%2C%20thereby%20changing%20the%20ratio%20between%20the%20two%20and%20invalidating%20the%20old%20benchmark%20indicators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFurther%20issues%20with%20quarterly%20data%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problems%20related%20to%20methodological%20issues%20were%20compounded%20by%20the%20data%20deficiencies.%20Even%20for%20the%20organised%20sector%2C%20only%20limited%20data%20is%20available.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20corporate%20sector%20data%20representing%20industry%20is%20available%20only%20for%20a%20few%20hundred%20firms.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20agriculture%2C%20it%20is%20assumed%20that%20targets%20set%20by%20the%20ministry%20are%20achieved.%20But%20that%20has%20not%20been%20the%20case%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years%20due%20to%20heat%20or%20late%20rains%20or%20inability%20of%20perishable%20crops%20to%20come%20to%20the%20market%20during%20the%20lockdown%20and%20demonetisation%2C%20so%20that%20it%20rotted%20in%20the%20fields%20and%20agricultural%20output%20declined%20while%20it%20was%20taken%20to%20have%20increased.%20The%20method%20for%20estimating%20the%20unorganised%20sector%20in%20the%20GDP%20needed%20to%20be%20modified%2C%20but%20this%20has%20not%20been%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20brief%2C%20there%20are%20two%20inter-related%20problems%20with%20the%20GDP%20data.%20The%20infirmity%20in%20the%20data%20and%20the%20invalidity%20of%20the%20method%20to%20calculate%20the%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20was%20further%20compounded%20by%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20lack%20of%20faith%20in%20its%20own%20employment%20data%20which%20it%20rejected%20in%202019%20because%20it%20showed%20that%20unemployment%20had%20reached%20a%20high%20of%2045%20years.%20Since%20employment%20data%20is%20used%20in%20the%20calculation%20of%20the%20GDP%2C%20if%20it%20is%20rejected%2C%20the%20GDP%20calculation%20also%20becomes%20unreliable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20persist%20with%20the%20methodology%20in%20the%202017%20official%20document%2C%20new%20indicators%20are%20required%20based%20on%20fresh%20surveys.%20But%20no%20new%20survey%20of%20the%20unorganised%20sector%20has%20been%20conducted%20since%202015.%20Even%20the%20Census%20has%20not%20been%20conducted%20in%202021%20and%20that%20compounds%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20each%20of%20the%20shocks%20listed%20above%20impacted%20the%20economy%20differently.%20So%2C%20without%20a%20change%20in%20the%20method%20and%20resolving%20the%20data%20issues%2C%20errors%20get%20compounded%20and%20reliable%20GDP%20numbers%20cannot%20be%20generated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStance%20of%20international%20agencies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20claims%20that%20international%20agencies%2C%20like%20the%20IMF%20and%20the%20UN%2C%20have%20supported%20its%20claims%20on%20GDP.%20Their%20figures%20for%20GDP%20growth%20differ%20from%20the%20official%20figures%20by%20a%20small%20percent.%20But%20that%20is%20not%20surprising%20since%20these%20agencies%20are%20not%20data%20collecting%20agencies%20and%20use%20the%20official%20data.%20Even%20the%20RBI%20uses%20the%20official%20data%20on%20a%20host%20of%20macro%20variables.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEffectively%2C%20all%20of%20them%20reproduce%20the%20errors%20in%20the%20official%20data%20and%20none%20of%20them%20have%20more%20accurate%20data.%20The%20surprise%20is%20that%20all%20these%20agencies%20ignore%20the%20data-related%20issues%20when%20the%20errors%20are%20glaring.%20Worse%2C%20if%20Indian%20data%20has%20such%20huge%20errors%2C%20other%20developing%20countries%20are%20likely%20to%20have%20similar%20or%20even%20greater%20errors%2C%20making%20international%20comparisons%20meaningless.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImpact%20on%20other%20macro%20aggregates%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGDP%20data%20is%20the%20base%20used%20to%20estimate%20other%20macro%20aggregates%2C%20like%20consumption%20and%20savings.%20These%20affect%20the%20measurement%20of%20poverty%20and%20growing%20inequality.%20If%20growth%20is%20strong%20then%20it%20would%20imply%20strong%20growth%20in%20employment.%20But%20this%20link%20is%20broken%20since%20growth%20is%20in%20the%20organised%20sector%20while%20the%20unorganised%20sector%20is%20declining.%20The%20former%20hardly%20creates%20employment%20while%20the%20latter%20which%20provides%20a%20bulk%20of%20the%20employment%20is%20losing%20employment.%20So%2C%20this%20lopsided%20growth%20has%20broken%20the%20link%20between%20growth%20and%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20if%20the%20unorganised%20sector%20declines%20then%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rbi.org.in%2FScripts%2FPublicationsView.aspx%3Fid%3D19331%5C%22%3Eoverall%20demand%20becomes%20short%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20leading%20to%20low%20capacity%20utilisation%20and%20decline%20in%20the%20investment%20rate%20and%20even%20the%20organised%20sector%20rate%20of%20growth%20will%20fall.%20This%20was%20visible%20in%20the%20period%202017-18%20and%202019-20%20(before%20the%20pandemic).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20incorrect%20GDP%20numbers%20should%20impact%20the%20fiscal%20situation.%20This%20is%20reflected%20in%20the%20revenue%20and%20expenditures%20often%20missing%20the%20targets%20set%20in%20the%20budget.%20The%20final%20figures%20differ%20considerably%20from%20the%20budget%20and%20revised%20estimates.%20But%20these%20revisions%20are%20not%20as%20stark%20as%20the%20errors%20in%20the%20GDP%20data%20should%20lead%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20for%20this%20smaller%20error%20is%20that%20the%20budget%20is%20largely%20for%20the%20organised%20sectors%20and%20of%20the%20organised%20sector.%20The%20revenue%20collection%20is%20largely%20from%20the%20organised%20sector.%20Most%20expenditures%20are%20also%20for%20the%20organised%20sector.%20Where%20the%20expenditures%20pertain%20to%20the%20unorganised%20sectors%20like%20on%20food%2C%20rural%20development%2C%20education%20and%20health%2C%20revisions%20are%20made%20when%20the%20deficit%20in%20the%20budget%20increases.%20Thus%2C%20the%20budgetary%20calculus%20is%20not%20as%20seriously%20impacted%20as%20the%20large%20errors%20in%20GDP%20data%20ought%20to%20lead%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConclusion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20conclude%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP%20numbers%20are%20vitiated%20due%20to%20methodological%20and%20data-related%20deficiencies.%20This%20suits%20the%20ruling%20party%E2%80%99s%20political%20narrative%20of%20a%20well-functioning%20economy.%20By%20continuing%20to%20harp%20on%20these%20incorrect%20numbers%20and%20hiding%20the%20true%20facts%2C%20it%20adds%20to%20the%20non-transparency%20in%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20functioning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EArun%20Kumar%20is%20the%20author%20of%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EUnderstanding%20Black%20Economy%20and%20Black%20Money%20in%20India%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704341107000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F04093406%2Fmaxim-potyomkin-imviVpdI1OM-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhat-do-we-really-know-about-indias-gdp%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20are%20two%20inter-related%20problems%20with%20the%20GDP%20data.%20The%20infirmity%20in%20the%20data%20and%20the%20invalidity%20of%20the%20method%20to%20calculate%20the%20GDP.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhat-do-we-really-know-about-indias-gdp%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Girl%20sings%20in%20140%20languages%20at%20concert%2C%20sets%20Guinness%20record%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704341012000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106531690%2Cimgsize-23012.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fkozhikode%2Fkannur-girl-sings-in-140-languages-at-concert-sets-guinness-record%2Farticleshow%2F106531646.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TNN%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fkozhikode%2Fkannur-girl-sings-in-140-languages-at-concert-sets-guinness-record%2Farticleshow%2F106531646.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Introducing%3A%20India%20Black%20Boxed%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03150057%2Fdavid-werbrouck-5GwLlb-_UYk-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EA%20breathtakingly%20audacious%20strategy%20deployed%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20over%20nearly%20a%20decade%20of%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%E2%80%99s%20rule%20is%20to%20simply%20keep%20the%20citizenry%20fed%20on%20multiple%20narratives%20which%20may%20not%20be%20supported%20by%20data%20or%20factual%20content.%20In%20this%20method%2C%20which%20has%20no%20precedent%2C%20the%20narrative%20is%20necessarily%20and%20systematically%20rendered%20bereft%20of%20any%20real%20content.%20This%20is%20achieved%20first%20and%20foremost%20by%20totally%20subverting%20transparency%20in%20politics%2C%20governance%20and%20policy%20making.%20This%20then%20becomes%20an%20essential%20precondition%20for%20the%20grand%20narrative%20to%20perpetuate%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20300px)%2085vw%2C%20300px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03150954%2FPrism.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03150954%2FPrism.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03150954%2FPrism-150x150.png%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691446%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3EThe%20result%20is%20an%20ever-widening%20gap%20between%20rhetoric%20and%20reality%2C%20as%20story%20after%20fanciful%20story%20plays%20out%20before%20the%20citizens%20even%20as%20institutions%20of%20transparency%20and%20accountability%20get%20upended.%20Some%20instances%20of%20the%20bogus%20narrative%20building%20by%20the%20government%20are%20so%20stark%20as%20to%20get%20exposed%20by%20subsequent%20events%20or%20actions.%20For%20example%20just%20recently%2C%20a%20preview%20of%20a%20book%20written%20by%20former%20Chief%20of%20Army%20General%20Manoj%20Naravane%20revealed%20how%20the%20controversial%20Agniveer%20scheme%20was%20imposed%20on%20the%20armed%20forces%20without%20any%20consultation.%20The%20impression%20given%20was%20that%20the%20forces%20had%20designed%20the%20recruitment%20scheme%20but%20that%20was%20not%20so.%20He%20also%20revealed%20the%20political%20leadership%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20courage%20to%20tell%20the%20army%20what%20should%20be%20done%20to%20respond%20to%20Chinese%20incursions%20on%20the%20Ladakh%20border.%20The%20defence%20minister%20merely%20told%20the%20army%20chief%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdo%20whatever%20he%20felt%20was%20necessary%E2%80%9D.%20In%20contrast%2C%20the%20narrative%20built%20was%20that%20the%20Modi%20regime%20was%20giving%20China%20a%20fitting%20reply.%20Similarly%20there%20is%20the%20perpetual%20narrative%20that%20every%20thing%20is%20peaceful%20in%20Kashmir%20and%20Manipur.%20No%20details%20or%20facts%20are%20forthcoming%20to%20support%20this%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20economic%20front%2C%20everything%20is%20hunky%20dory.%20India%20is%20the%20fastest%20growing%20economy%20in%20the%20world%2C%20never%20mind%20free%20ration%20for%2080%20crore%20people%20is%20extended%20by%20Modi%20as%20a%20guarantee%20for%20another%20five%20years.%20The%20unemployment%20rate%2C%20we%20are%20told%2C%20is%20at%20an%20all-time%20low%20but%20the%20army%20of%20unpaid%20workers%20shown%20as%20employed%20has%20doubled%20in%20the%20past%20five%20years.%20GDP%20growth%20is%20being%20questioned%20by%20well-known%20economists%20but%20the%20government%20steadfastly%20holds%20on%20to%20its%